### Variables
### Run "Login" first; then use accessToken. Set friendId to a user ID that is already your friend (ACCEPTED).
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@accessToken = {{login.response.body.accessToken}}
@friendId = bc9aa392-7151-4671-8b76-e73c24758b5c
@channelId = {{createDirect.response.body.id}}

### 1. Login (run this first to get accessToken)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test1@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### 2. Create or get direct channel with a friend (body: friendId)
### Replace friendId above with a user ID that is already your friend.
# @name createDirect
POST {{baseUrl}}/channel/direct
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "friendId": "{{friendId}}"
}

### 3. List my direct channels (paginated)
GET {{baseUrl}}/channel/direct?limit=20&page=1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 4. Get channel by ID (use channelId from step 2, or set @channelId manually)
GET {{baseUrl}}/channel/{{channelId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 5. Send a message to the channel
POST {{baseUrl}}/channel/{{channelId}}/messages
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "content": "I already sent a message to you. Have you received it?"
}

### 6. Get messages in the channel (paginated)
GET {{baseUrl}}/channel/{{channelId}}/messages?limit=20&page=1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### --- Manual override: set channelId and token by hand ---
# @name getChannel
# GET {{baseUrl}}/channel/YOUR_CHANNEL_ID_HERE
# Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

# @name sendMessage
# POST {{baseUrl}}/channel/YOUR_CHANNEL_ID_HERE/messages
# Content-Type: application/json
# Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
#
# {
#   "content": "Hello!"
# }

# @name getMessages
# GET {{baseUrl}}/channel/YOUR_CHANNEL_ID_HERE/messages?limit=20&page=1
# Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
